A comprehensive tutorial covering the fundamentals and advanced techniques for human activity recognition using deep learning.

## Topics Covered

- Data preparation and preprocessing for video data
- CNN architectures for temporal modeling
- Transformer-based approaches for action recognition
- Multi-view fusion techniques
- Real-time inference optimization
- Evaluation metrics and benchmarking

## Prerequisites

- Python programming
- Basic deep learning knowledge
- Familiarity with PyTorch

## Learning Outcomes

By completing this tutorial, you will be able to:
- Build end-to-end HAR systems
- Implement state-of-the-art architectures
- Optimize models for edge deployment
- Evaluate model performance properly

